<DocsLayout title="§1 Robot URI (RURI)" description="RCAN §1 — Robot URI (RURI). Every robot on the RCAN network has a globally unique Robot URI (RURI). This section defines the two syntactic forms — canonical (with registry) and local shorthand — along with component definitions, validation regex patterns, and wildcard matching rules for JWT audience claims.">
  <div class="flex items-center gap-4 mb-4">
    <h1 class="mb-0">§1 Robot URI (RURI)</h1>
  </div>
  <div class="flex gap-2 mb-8 flex-wrap">
    <span class="inline-flex items-center px-2.5 py-0.5 rounded-full text-xs font-medium bg-green-500/10 text-green-400 border border-green-500/20">
      Status: Stable
    </span>
    <span class="inline-flex items-center px-2.5 py-0.5 rounded-full text-xs font-medium bg-accent/10 text-accent border border-accent/20">
      RCAN v1.3
    </span>
    <a href="/spec/" class="inline-flex items-center px-2.5 py-0.5 rounded-full text-xs font-medium bg-white/5 text-text-muted border border-white/10 hover:border-white/20">
      ← Back to Specification
    </a>
  </div>

  <div class="not-prose bg-cyan-500/5 border border-cyan-500/20 rounded-xl p-6 mb-10">
    <p class="text-sm text-cyan-300/80">
      <strong class="text-cyan-400">Overview:</strong> Every robot on the RCAN network has a globally unique Robot URI (RURI). This section defines the two syntactic forms — canonical (with registry) and local shorthand — along with component definitions, validation regex patterns, and wildcard matching rules for JWT audience claims.
    </p>
